Codename: Ainsbrook
A Time Team Special
First screened 14 January 2008


In late 2003 two metal detectorists were working in a field in Yorkshire. They found &#039;treasure&#039; buried just beneath the surface ? a collection of Viking material next to a body. Although they had been detecting on the site for a number of years, during which time they had made large numbers of finds, nothing they had uncovered previously compared with this. They decided to share their discovery with archaeologists.
